Topic.Title: On the third day of sequester Obama gave to me:

Message.Msg: "spending over the last several or more years is adding a trillion dollars or so a year to the deficit" Because *spending* is not adding a trillion dollars or so a year to the deficit. The trillion dollar increase is a combination of spending, tax cuts and reduced revenue from the recession. Most of the spending increase is temporary--TARP, stimulus, etc. Likewise the Bush tax cuts were responsible for most of the deficit through the 2000s. That's what "Starve the Beast" means. You cut taxes to create a deficit that you hope will result in spending cuts. Republicans do this not because they're concerned about a balanced budget. They have an ideological notion about the "size" of government. Remember how Clinton achieved a surplus? Tax increases, economic growth, and slowing long term spending growth. He did not "cut spending". Our economy can definitely handle the level of government spending we have now. Our people have consistently demanded it. We need to pay for it, keep spending growth restrained, and prioritize our spending.
